===Etymology===
English, from [[cellular]], and [[telephone]].

=== Noun ===
'''cell phone''' (''plural'' '''cell phones''')
#A [[portable]], [[wireless]] [[telephone]], which changes [[antenna]] connections [[seamlessly]] during [[travel]] from one radio reception [[cell]] to another without losing the party-to-party [[call]] [[connection]].
===Synonyms===
*[[mobile]] (''note'': word used in the UK and AUS)
*[[cellphone]], [[cell-phone]], (''note'': word used in the US)
*[[cellular mobile]], [[cellular]], [[cellular telephone]]
*[[wireless phone]]

